---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`Privacy Policy for ${SITE_NAME}.`}
>
  <article class="article">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="article__meta" style="border: 0; padding: 0; margin-top: -0.25rem;">
      Last updated: July 19th, 2026
    </p>
    <div class="article__body">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how {SITE_NAME} (“we”, “us”) collects and
        uses information when you visit the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is owned and operated by <strong>AK Ventures Inc.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <h3>Analytics</h3>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Google Analytics</strong> (Google LLC) to understand how
        visitors use the Site. Google Analytics collects information such as
        pages viewed, approximate location derived from IP address, device and
        browser type, and referral source. Google may process this data on our
        behalf under its own terms and privacy policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our Google Analytics measurement ID is <code>G-JZV2D683SW</code>.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can learn more about Google Analytics and how to opt out in
        Google’s documentation, including the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser
        Add-on where available.
      </p>

      <h3>Email</h3>
      <p>
        If you subscribe to email updates, we collect the email address you
        provide and use it to send those updates (and related list management),
        unless you consent to something else. Email signup is handled by{' '}
        <strong>Beehiiv</strong>. See Beehiiv’s privacy policy for how they
        process subscriber data on our behalf.
      </p>

      <h3>Server and security logs</h3>
      <p>
        Our hosting provider may automatically process technical logs (for
        example IP address, timestamps, and request URLs) needed to operate and
        secure the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
      <p>
        Google Analytics may set cookies or use similar technologies to
        distinguish visits and measure traffic. You can control cookies through
        your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To measure and improve the Site</li>
        <li>To understand which stories attract readers</li>
        <li>To send email you asked for (when applicable)</li>
        <li>To maintain security and troubleshoot issues</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We share data with service
        providers who help us run the Site (including Google for Analytics and
        our hosting provider), only as needed for those services.
      </p>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Analytics data is retained according to our Google Analytics settings
        and Google’s policies. Email subscription data is kept until you
        unsubscribe or we close the list.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You can block analytics cookies in your browser, use Google’s opt-out
        tools where available, and unsubscribe from email using the link in any
        message we send.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from them.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date at
        the top will change when we do.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, email{' '}
        <a href="mailto:info@travelnewsradar.com">info@travelnewsradar.com</a>
        {' '}or see our <a href="/contact/">Contact</a> page.
      </p>

      <p>
        <em
          >This is an initial policy for site launch and may be expanded as
          features (such as email capture) go live.</em
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
